item.title: Variables and Types
item.description: Variables and Types You do not need to declare variables before using them or declare their type. Every variable in Python is an object. Variables can hold any value and are case-sensitive. This tutorial will go over a few basic types of variables. Variable Names There are a number of rules governing the naming of variables: 1.
